title: About Me
text:
I am a full-time PhD student in the Linguistics Department at University of California, Davis. I work at the Corina Neurolinguistics Lab. I currently am studying conduction aphasia and language production and perception as it relates to sign language. In my free time, I like to hike and photograph mushrooms.
Education:
University of California, Davis | PhD in Linguistics (Current)
The Ohio State University | Bachelor of Arts Psychology and Linguistics
